<dl id="n22044d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22044d">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22044d"> 44(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> light candle / at fire</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">While she was feasting there, the merchant came home after supper, full of spite and anger about the lamprey, and to execute the plan he had conceived, took his rods in his hand and then searched for a light for the candle, but found no fire even in the chimney <small> Robert B. Douglas, trans., <a name="RBDM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBDM"><cite title="source">ONE HUNDRED MERRIE AND DELIGHTSOME STORIES</cite></a> (1923) Story 38</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
